A much larger map for GG diesgned for a maximum of 64 players. Buyzones are in place for those who want to use this for normal servers as well, goes well as an aim or fy or dm map too I suppose. Large simple and spaced out design to give lots of room and at the same time still adaquate cover for those who want to :D
People should be getting high-average frames in most places, other than of course in top corners of the map looking at everything on a full server might drop it down heh, The initial creation of this map took only a day, but its been maybe a week or two of tweaking and adding and just basically optimising and making it look really cool heh. for those following once again the wait is over :D If your going to add this map to your server please post an ip for anyone else interested in in, ours can be found at http://WMD-CLAN.com but its only a 20 man server and spots do tend to fill up quickly on popular maps. well, hope you all enjoy and keep the comments coming
fyi, I know about some of the missing squares, I kinda went over my maximun number of brushes, whoopse :P so had to get rid of some but I don't think it takes too much away from the map.

Latest of the WMD series of maps.
Once again its another quick little Gun Game map that I've whipped up to play on our gun game servers, inside the file is also the txt file for GG DM spawnpoints for servers running that version of the mod, it will work in both normal gungame and DM.
This map can be run at hightest graphics settings and still be smooth on most average gaming computers. At low they will simply be phenominal but lack the nice look of the map obvisially. Radar and custom textures are included within the bsp as well to keep everything clean. Nav file is also included for convience.
For those who have been watching for the past week you now have the chance to play it.
Its currently on two of our servers: 69.65.14.206:27015 Weapons of Mass Destruction - GunGame Deathmatch 205.234.203.141:27015 Weapons of Mass Destruction - GunGame Turbo (HLStatsX) So pop in and play both styles of the game, each has its quirks :P
Also, since I don't have any real immediate projects on the go I can accept Gun Game map requests/ideas via Half Life Storm studios. Lost,

Continuing on my one day random build of a map, Total time current sits at 8 hours work, This is not meant to be a final version, far from it, All that has been added since last version is better visleafs and optimized brushs, a CT side built and sides expanded farther out by a few units. Still need to incorporate some form of cover to the sides a bit and finish off something of a 3d skybox I think. There are errors still in the map, noticed them in my first few times loading it, ie CT spawn building, bad reflects due to no cubemaps and func_details. Along with misshapen brush's here and there that need to be fixed. Map is not done, map is NOT Perfect so no 10's this time around please.... Enjoy and feel free to send feedback and ideas to myself if you wish, Logan "TheLost" Dougall (ghost.in.the.crowd@gmail.com)

A medium sized Gun Game Map, Very straightforward gameplay here, no real easy way to hide from people or for very long. Simple three level system here, ground floor, a few things to stand on and 4 walkways at medium hight and two parralel platforms at the very top in the middle.
Map concept time for this didn't take too long, neither did construction or compiling so this was a pretty quick release here. Next maps for this game type will be same size or smaller for quicker rounds as its been requested many times by people here and also on our GG server.
Nav file and any other nessasary files are included inside the bsp so don't say I forgot it cause it is there heh. should be no problems on that end. Just note that bots rarly if ever use the upper floors which is nicer for people because that would just slow the game down if they are stuck agaist only bots :P well, enjoy the map, going to probally finish up another one this weekend, Lost,

GG WMD CELLULAR ~Map Created by Lost ( Logan Dougall ) The First Map Developed for CSS that has full and working Cellshading effect. This had origninaly just started out as an engine test but then soon progressed into a fully functional map. This is a smaller stage than the other WMD maps that proceeded this, as its been requested. So it will run better on smaller servers rather than large 30+ servers as it would get cramped and loose its charm quickly. Its been about a month since I started working on this idea and I think I've molded it as best as I can for the first forray into this style of maps, and I will be creating a few more over the next few weeks to get them out there and onto some servers. They will still have extra little things in them with my own style of course, I still dread the day where I snap and make a simple 6 block map lol, but I'll still have some interesting ones out in the next little while so keep and eye out for them and see any WIP through Half Life Storm Studios of course and what the rest of them are doing as well. Feel free to vote HLS mapping studio of the month again :D Lastly, I'd recommend taking a look over at A.Werner's map done in my same style but re-mixed so to speak. I quite like how he took the basic idea I've presented here and added his own style. Well worth your time:
gg_edgecl Cell Shaded Effect Tutorial Enjoy, Lost,

This one has taken quite a bit more work than I'm used to. Learning new techiques/options that I've never had to take before. I've been taking all the advice given to me by the people here and also within wmd and the gun game regulars. I'm getting better at making maps to suit the players and this one is another step towards that. I hope people enjoy it. Enjoy the map and feel free to stop by our WMD Run servers anytime you wish. If you have map ideas/suggestions feel free to contact me at Lost.0wned.ca Quick Info: Edited .Nav file to better conform to bot use for servers. Bziped for fastdownload enabled servers. All required files packed into the bsp to help tidy things up. 3D Skybox Grass Detail effect Radar Overview (Nothing fancy) HDR (Glitchy in basement) Optmisation of both Geomentry and Models for Fps boost Love and care then the boot out the door... ;) Thanks to the support from the o'l WMD gang and the fellow mappers from FPSB. Stay tuned, theres more to come, Lost, *quite honestly I was feeling like I was getting stuck on this and need to move onto my other projects while I have the ball rolling here :P
